<s1 id=ChangeFontTypeTA> To Select a Font Group
 
        <idx|font: selecting new type|
        <idx|selecting: font type|
        <idx|Font dialog box|
        <idx|dialog box: Font|
 
<list order>
 
* Click the Style Manager Font control.
 
* Select a font type under Font Group.

* Look at the Preview window labels and text, which show the new font typeface.
 
* Click OK to enable newly-started applications to use the selected typeface,
or click Cancel to cancel the operation.
 
<\list>
 
 
<!-- <figure nonumber entity=FontDialogBox>
<\figure> -->
 
<procedure>See Also

<list bullet tight>

* <xref SMFontDialogDE>

<\list>

<s1 id=UpdatePreviewWindowTA>To Update Preview Window

<list order>
 
* Click the Style Manager Font control.
 
* Click on a Font Group and a Size in the scrolling lists at the top of the
Font dialog box.
<\list>

The Preview Window area reflects the scrolling list selections.



<s1 id=AddFontGroupTA>To Add a Font Group
<list order>
 
* Click the Style Manager Font control.
 
* Press the Add button on the Font dialog box.

* Choose a font group from the System scrolling list and a font group from
the User scrolling list. 

* Press OK to open the Font Group Name dialog box. (Press Cancel to cancel 
the operation and close the dialog box.)

* Enter a name in the New Font Group Name field of the Font Group Name 
dialog box for the new font group. You can enter any non-blank name that you
want.

* Press OK to add a font group to the Font dialog box scrolling list. 
Press Cancel to cancel the operation.

<\list>




<s1 id=DeleteFontGroupTA>To Delete a Font Group
<list order>
 
* Click the Style Manager Font control.

* Select a font group from the Font Group scrolling list on the Font dialog box.
 
* Press the Delete button. The Delete Font Group dialog box appears.

* Press OK to delete the font group from the Font Group scrolling list.
Press Cancel to cancel the operation.
<\list>



